               <msContents class="#CM">
                  <summary><p>A composite manuscript, described here as a multi-text manuscript for the sake of convenience. The leaves are rolled and thus not easily legible. It seems that there are three different texts:
<list>
  <item>U1.</item>
  <item>U2. Probably a Christian text as the word <foreign xml:lang="ta">kiṟist=tu</foreign> appears in it. </item>
  <item>U3. By a Christian copyist. See left-marginal blessing <foreign xml:lang="ta">yēcu tuṇai</foreign> of f1r. A calendar or a diary.</item>
    </list>
</p>
<p>Description based on the examination of the original manuscript (September 2020).</p>
<p>Dimensions after Cabaton (1912). Due to the fact that the leaves are rolled, dimensions could not be assessed at the time of examination.</p>  </summary>
                  
